FBIS4-23180 "drafr104_c_94031" FBIS-AFR-94-104 Daily Report 29 May 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Pik Botha Elected in PWV Pik Botha Elected in PWV MB2905071794 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 0600 GMT 29 May 94 MB2905071794 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] Mineral and Energy Affairs minister Pik Botha has been elected NP [National Party] leader in the PWV [Pretoria, Witwatersrand, Vereeniging] region. He defeated Constitutional Development and Provincial Affairs Minister Roelf Meyer in an election at the last Transvaal NP congress under the old dispensation. Mr. Meyer obtained fewer than 10 percent of the votes.
